Installation Instructions
=========================

The CernVM-FS build system uses cmake.  

IN order to corerctly build the system several dependencies are necessary, in a 
ubuntu based system you can get them using:

 	sudo apt-get install \ 
		python-dev \
		zlib1g-dev \
		libssl-dev \
		uuid-dev \
		libfuse-dev \
		libcap-dev \
		libattr1-dev \
		unzip

On CentOS like system you can get them using

	sudo yum install 
		python-devel \
		zlib-devel \
		libattr-devel \
		openssl-devel \
		libuuid-devel
		fuse-devel \
		libcap-devel

In order to compile and install, run from the source directory

    mkdir -p build
    cd build
    cmake ../
    make
    sudo make install

In order to build the unit tests in addition, use
`cmake -DBUILD_UNITTESTS=yes ../`

For more details, please see the [technical documentation](https://cvmfs.readthedocs.io/en/stable/).

